People in the emerging world of today want a high standard of living. More and more
household appliances are being incorporated into structures that offer a high standard of life. How
therefore should this adaptable equipment be controlled and managed at home? Typically,
traditional wall switches are placed in various rooms of a house and need manual actions, such as
pressing to turn on the lights, or human effort. Operating becomes challenging for elderly or
physically challenged folks. The main objective of home automation is to help handicapped and
aged technology to control home appliances, automate regular works and alert them in critical
situations
